  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      China's VR industry is booming, but it also faces many problems. At present, industry&#xD;
      standards for key physical parameters of virtual reality are still being explored. More and&#xD;
      more attention has been paid to the visual health and safety of VR. Based on&#xD;
      ophthalmology-neurologic technology, this study screened VR ocular safety parameters,&#xD;
      constructed VR evaluation model and provided visual health evaluation system and standards&#xD;
      for VR technology.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
